23/09/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano reiterated on Wednesday (22 September) that NATO integration is the government's main priority. In an address to the UN General Assembly, he said the country is implementing necessary reforms on the road to Euro-Atlantic integration and is working to harmonise legislation with EU standards, while strengthening democracy and public institutions. He also pledged to secure free and democratic elections in 2005, in line with OSCE recommendations. (Albanian Daily News - 23/09/04; ATA - 22/09/04)
